  "description": "<p><u><strong>Job Description</strong></u></p>\n<p>- Adopt innovative teaching methods and create an engaging learning experience for children/youths</p>\n<p>- Create worksheets and lesson material</p>\n<p>- Prepare and deliver lessons that facilitate active learning experiences<br>\n- Perform required classroom administration responsibilities</p>\n<p>- Maintain a professional and proactive relationship with caseworkers</p>\n<p><u><strong>Job Requirements</strong></u></p>\n<p>- Bachelor's degree or equivalent</p>\n<p>- Up-to-date with the latest MOE syllabus</p>\n<p>- At least 2-3 years of relevant teaching experience</p>\n<p>- Passion for teaching and nurturing students</p>\n<p>- Able to travel</p>\n<p>- Pleasant and friendly personality</p>\n<p>- Lesson timings would be anytime between 2pm – 9pm on weekdays during school term, depending on the availability of clients</p>\n<p><u><strong>Rate:</strong></u></p>\n<p>Hourly rate of $30 to $75</p>",
